==English==
===Pronunciation===
* (shô)
* {{IPA|/ˈʃɑː/}} ''(US)''
* {{IPA|/pʃɔ:/}} ''(RP)''
*{{audio|en-us-pshaw.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Interjection===
'''pshaw'''
# indicating [[disapproval]], [[irritation]], [[impatience]] or [[disbelief]].
#:''Pshaw! I can't believe It!''

====Quotations====
{{timeline|
1800s=1823 1838 1891 1992}}
*'''1823''' — [[w:James Fenimore Cooper|James Fenimore Cooper]], ''[[s:The_Pioneers|The Pioneers]]'', ch. 13
*:"'''Pshaw'''! Why do ye bother yourself wid texts, man, about so small a matter?" interrupted the landlady
*'''1838-1839''' — [[w:Charles_Dickens|Charles Dickens]], ''[[s:Nicholas Nickleby|Nicholas Nickleby]]'', ch. 56
*:''''Pshaw'''!' Ralph muttered, forcing a laugh.
*'''1891''' — [[w:Arthur Conan Doyle|Arthur Conan Doyle]], ''[[s:The_White_Company|The White Company]]'', ch. xxiii
*:"Have a care, cousin," he whispered; "for the sake of the Virgin have a care, for you have angered him."
*:"'''Pshaw'''! fear not," the other answered in the same low tone.
*'''1992''' - Wayne Campbell, ''[[w:Wayne's World (film)|Wayne's World]]''
*:"'''Pshaw'''! And monkeys might fly out of my butt."

